meanings.definition: past tense of outlearn: to surpass in learning or knowledge.
meanings.sent1: She outlearnt her classmates in math and science.
meanings.sent2: He outlearnt all his competitors in the spelling bee.
meanings.sent3: The young student outlearnt the old professor in solving the puzzle.
meanings.sent4: Her dedication to studying outlearnt any obstacles in her way.
meanings.sent5: The explorer outlearnt the dangers of the jungle through experience.
